2019s innovative new product, the HCM Cloud. Oracle\u2019s HCM offerings support Benefits Management, Compensation Management, Payroll Processing, Talent Management and other essential elements of strategic human resources management. Oracle\u2019s Cloud offerings leverage the technologies accelerating modern business including Big Data Analytics, AI, Blockchain and others. Analytical Capabilities: Throughout the implementation cycle for HCM deployments, ArcLight consultants are challenged to break down and clarify difficult concepts for customers and \u2018dig in\u2019 and build out Oracle\u2019s Cloud modules. As you design, test and implement Oracle\u2019s Cloud solutions, considerations of the potential downstream impacts of decisions ensure the capabilities you\u2019ve designed and delivered are robust, sustainable, and readily adaptable to future needs. Process Improvement: Work with peers to continuously improve ArcLight\u2019s delivery methodologies and tools. Contribute to enhancing ArcLight\u2019s value proposition for clients through process efficiencies, design excellence, quality assurance and deep functional and technical knowledge. Benefits & Career Advancement: Competitive compensation structure (top of market) Quarterly / Annual bonus program rewarding individual efforts and company progress Medical, Dental, Vision coverage 401(k) retirement plan Life insurance benefits Volunteer Time allowance Cell Phone and internet reimbursement Charitable contribution program 3 Weeks PTO program Floating holidays / Company holidays Qualifications: 0-2 years of experience Knowledge of HR processes preferred Interpersonal, communication and presentation skills Self-motivated and able to plan work effort and manage priorities Keen attention to detail Intermediate to expert level excel skills. PowerPoint / Word experience a plus. Strong academic performance Willing to learn a range of business or technical specialties based on business needs Demonstrated ability to 